&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Try this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT
    C.cart_id,
    I.item_id,
    C.quantity,
    COALESCE(I.discounted_price, I.price) AS price
FROM
    cart C,
    item I
WHERE
    I.item_id = C.item_id
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/4.1/en/comparison-operators.html#function_coalesce" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;code&gt;COALESCE&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; selects the first non null value from a list of arguments. That is, when discount_price is NULL, it returns price.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If your 'null' value is 0.00, you can use this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT
    C.cart_id,
    I.item_id,
    C.quantity,
    IF(I.discounted_price &amp;gt; 0, I.discounted_price, I.price) AS price
    ...
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is, if discounted price is greater than zero, use that, otherwise use the normal price.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="language-c"&gt;int a&lt;span class="hljs-punctuation"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;b&lt;span class="hljs-punctuation"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-keyword"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-punctuation"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;d&lt;span class="hljs-comment"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
