&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;preg_match('/^[\w]{4,35}$/i', $username)
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OK lets see what this doesn't work : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Match the beginning of the string, followed by [a-zA-Z0-9_] at least 4 times with a maximum of 35 times. This is quite different from your requirements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead what you should use : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;/^[a-zA-Z][-,.\w]{3,34}$/
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The case sensitivity i modifier is not needed. Also I don't think this is exactly what you want. Usually you would need to specify a minimum length which you don't. This can match "a" for example (&lt;em&gt;not a good username&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
